  schema:name "Covenant Platform: A Model of Christian Charity as the First Social Media" ;
  schema:description "Social media's participatory, algorithmic, and performative logics descend from Reformation-era systems of liturgical replication, visibility, and communal surveillance. Winthrop's 1630 sermon is the inaugural social media post: a performative declaration encoding an algorithm of divine attention." ;
